cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.GR 

This paper deals with image deblurring, which is a common problem in computer vision and image processing. The use of graphs and total variation suggests that it may fall under the categories of computer vision (cs.CV), multimedia (cs.MM), information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), or graphics (cs.GR). However, given the focus on image processing and restoration, cs.CV is the most likely category.
